# ioBroker.autodarts

Connects ioBroker to the local [Autodarts Board Manager](https://autodarts.io) for electronic dartboards with automatic scoring. All data stays local (no cloud dependencies).

## Stack

- Plain **JavaScript** in `main.js` and `lib/` — no TypeScript build step; optional `npm run check` (JSDoc/types via `tsconfig.check.json`)
- Admin UI via **jsonConfig** (`admin/jsonConfig.json`), not a compiled React frontend
- HTTP: native `node:http` via `lib/httpHelper.js` (no axios/request)
- Connection: local Board Manager REST API, HTTP polling (default port 3180)
- Extended docs: `docs/en/`, `docs/de/` (README is English only)

## Git (mandatory)

- **Never** run `git commit`, `git push`, or releases unless the user explicitly asks
- User commits and pushes; releases via `npm run release-*` (AlCalzone release-script)
- **Never** run `npm run translate` — owner runs it manually before release

## Changelog & README (mandatory for every change)

For **every code or config change**, update `README.md` before finishing:

1. Add a user-facing entry under `### **WORK IN PROGRESS**` (English)
2. Format: `- (skvarel) Plain description` — no bold prefixes (`**FIXED**`, `**NEW**`, etc.; breaks news translation)
3. Update README and **both** `docs/en/` and `docs/de/` when options, behavior, or data points change
4. Do **not** edit `CHANGELOG_OLD.md` manually — release-script moves older entries there

## Scope

- Minimal, focused diffs; match patterns in `main.js`, `lib/`, and `admin/`
- After every code change: run `npm run lint` and fix all warnings (CI uses `--max-warnings 0`)

## Local checks (optional, matches CI)

- `npm run lint`
- `npm run test` (`test:js` + `test:package`)

## Further rules

Detailed conventions live in `.cursor/rules/` (code, admin UI, testing, docs/CI, Autodarts patterns).
